        "text": "To show this, we check that the function f(x) = (1 1/x)*-1 is strictly decreasing for x > 1; while this can be achieved using the weighted arithmetic-geometric mean inequality, we give a simple calculus proof instead. The derivative of log f(x) is log (1 - 1/x) + 1/x, so it is enough to check that this is negative for x > 1. An equivalent statement is that log(1 - x) + x < 0 for 0 < x < 1; this in turn holds because the function g(x) = 1og(1 - x) + x tends to 0 as x → 0* and has derivative 1- I <0 for 0 <x<1.",
